## 1. Introduction

**Scope Boundary:** This TDD specifies HOW to implement the bug fix defined in the FSD. It does NOT repeat functional requirements, business rules, or use cases — refer to the FSD for those. This document focuses on: root cause analysis, code change design, implementation patterns, and testing strategy.

### 1.1 Purpose

This TDD provides the technical design for fixing the tool\_use\_id mismatch bug in the kiro-rs Anthropic converter module. The converter currently generates new IDs during response conversion, breaking the ReAct tool-calling loop. The fix ensures ID passthrough from the Kiro Q API response to both the SSE stream and conversation history.

### 1.2 Scope

| In Scope | Out of Scope |
| --- | --- |
| Fix converter.rs — remove ID generation, passthrough original ID | VS Code extension changes |
| Fix handlers.rs — ensure history stores same ID as streamed | Kiro Q API backend changes |
| Add diagnostic logging for tool\_use\_id at boundaries | Non-Anthropic format converters |
| Add descriptive error when ID mismatch detected | Tool discovery/registration |
| Unit and integration tests for the fix | Plain text streaming (already works) |

### 1.3 Technology Stack

| Layer | Technology | Version |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Language | Rust | 2021 Edition (stable) |
| Framework | Axum / Actix-web (HTTP) | Latest stable |
| Async Runtime | Tokio | 1.x |
| Serialization | serde / serde\_json | 1.x |
| Streaming | Server-Sent Events (SSE) | Custom impl |
| Testing | cargo test + tokio::test | Built-in |
| Build Tool | Cargo | Rust stable |

### 1.4 Design Principles

* **Zero-copy ID passthrough** — tool\_use\_id flows from API response to stream and history without transformation
* **Single source of truth** — the Kiro Q API is the sole authority for tool\_use\_id generation
* **Fail-fast with diagnostics** — invalid or missing IDs are caught immediately with actionable error messages
* **Thread safety** — conversation history accessed from async context must be safe under concurrent access
* **Backward compatible** — no changes to the SSE streaming format or extension API contract

### 1.5 Constraints

* kiro-rs is a Rust binary — all changes must compile with stable Rust toolchain
* No new external dependencies (crate additions) required for this fix
* The streaming response format to the extension MUST remain unchanged
* The fix must not introduce measurable latency (< 1ms overhead)

