## 12. Appendix

### Glossary

| Term | Definition |
| --- | --- |
| Passthrough | Design pattern where data flows unchanged between layers |
| tool\_use\_id | Unique identifier for a tool invocation, generated by Kiro Q API |
| SSE | Server-Sent Events — HTTP-based server push protocol |
| ReAct Loop | Reasoning + Acting: model reasons, calls tool, observes result, repeats |
| Continuation | Follow-up request containing tool execution results |

### Open Questions

| # | Question | Status | Answer |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| 1 | Is there a generate\_tool\_use\_id() function or is it inline UUID generation? | Open | DEV to confirm during implementation |
| 2 | Is ConversationHistory behind Arc or Arc? | Open | DEV to confirm — RwLock preferred for read-heavy access |
| 3 | Should tool\_use\_id format be strictly validated (regex) or just non-empty? | Resolved | Non-empty check only (BR-3). Format advisory, not enforced. |

